cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses instance-aware convolution, which involves learning instance-specific weights, indicating that it involves some level of machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also compares its results to other state-of-the-art methods, indicating that it involves some level of evaluation and comparison (cs.LG). The method is also applicable to both anchor-based and anchor-free frameworks, which are common in robotics and autonomous systems (cs.RO). Finally, the paper uses the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection and segmentation in multimedia (cs.MM).
